## 3. Define research question

In 2010, was county-average BMI associated with county-average annual PM2.5?

## 4. Review data structure

```{r}
summary(dta$AveBMI)

hist(dta$AveBMI, freq = FALSE, xlab = "Average BMI", ylab = "Density", las = 1)
lines(density(dta$AveBMI, na.rm = TRUE))

LargestBMI <- dta[dta$AveBMI == max(dta$AveBMI, na.rm = TRUE), ]
LargestBMI

plot(x = dta$AvePM,
     y = dta$AveBMI,
     xlab = expression("Average PM"[2.5]),
     ylab = "Average BMI",
     main = "Scatterplot: County-average PM2.5 vs. BMI")
```

> **Class questions**  

> - Are PM2.5 and BMI positively correlated?  
**Correlation:** PM2.5 and BMI appear **positively** correlated, but **not very strongly**.  

> - Does it look strongly correlated?  
**Visual strength:** The scatter suggests a **modest** relationship with substantial variability.  

> - Will the adjusted regression association equal the unadjusted correlation?
**Adjusted vs unadjusted:** The adjusted regression association will **not necessarily equal** the unadjusted correlation because regression **conditions on covariates** (confounding control), while correlation does not.


## 5. Fit regression model

```{r}
mod <- lm(AveBMI ~ AvePM + PerBlack + PerLatinx + PerAsianAm +
            MedHInc + MedHVal + LTHS + FemaleUnemp + MaleUnemp + ClimateRegion,
          data = dta,
          na.action = na.omit)
```

