## 8. Examine effect modification

Does the PM2.5–BMI association vary by climate region?

### 8a. Interaction model

```{r}
mod.interaction <- lm(AveBMI ~ AvePM * ClimateRegion + PerBlack + PerLatinx + PerAsianAm +
                        MedHInc + MedHVal + LTHS + FemaleUnemp + MaleUnemp,
                      data = dta.noOutliers, na.action = na.omit)

summary(mod.interaction)
```

### 8b. Within-region estimate (Upper Midwest example)

```{r}
coef.mat <- summary(mod.interaction)$coefficients
var.mat  <- vcov(mod.interaction)

beta.PM_upper_midwest <- coef.mat["AvePM", "Estimate"] +
  coef.mat["AvePM:ClimateRegionupper_midwest", "Estimate"]

var.PM_upper_midwest <- var.mat["AvePM", "AvePM"] +
  var.mat["AvePM:ClimateRegionupper_midwest", "AvePM:ClimateRegionupper_midwest"] +
  2 * var.mat["AvePM", "AvePM:ClimateRegionupper_midwest"]

se.PM_upper_midwest  <- sqrt(abs(var.PM_upper_midwest))
lci.PM_upper_midwest <- beta.PM_upper_midwest - 1.96 * se.PM_upper_midwest
uci.PM_upper_midwest <- beta.PM_upper_midwest + 1.96 * se.PM_upper_midwest

paste0(round(beta.PM_upper_midwest, 3),
       " (95% CI: ", round(lci.PM_upper_midwest, 3), ", ", round(uci.PM_upper_midwest, 3), ")")
```

### 8c. Likelihood ratio test

```{r}
anova(mod.noOutliers, mod.interaction, test = "LRT")
```

### 8d. Stratified model (Upper Midwest example)

```{r}
mod.stratified <- lm(AveBMI ~ AvePM + PerBlack + PerLatinx + PerAsianAm +
                       MedHInc + MedHVal + LTHS + FemaleUnemp + MaleUnemp,
                     data = dta.noOutliers, na.action = na.omit,
                     subset = (ClimateRegion == "upper_midwest"))

summary(mod.stratified)
```

## 9. Breakout exercises — answer key

### 9.1 What is the effect estimate (95% CI) for `MedHVal`?  

```{r}
broom::tidy(mod, conf.int = TRUE) |>
  dplyr::filter(term == "MedHVal") |>
  dplyr::transmute(
    term,
    estimate  = round(estimate, 4),
    conf.low  = round(conf.low, 4),
    conf.high = round(conf.high, 4)
  )
```

### 9.2 Compute the association and 95% CI for a **10 μg/m³** increase in `AvePM` in the main model.  

```{r}
pm <- broom::tidy(mod, conf.int = TRUE) |>
  dplyr::filter(term == "AvePM")

pm10 <- pm |>
  dplyr::mutate(
    estimate  = estimate  * 10,
    conf.low  = conf.low  * 10,
    conf.high = conf.high * 10
  ) |>
  dplyr::transmute(
    contrast = "10 μg/m³ increase in AvePM",
    estimate  = round(estimate, 4),
    conf.low  = round(conf.low, 4),
    conf.high = round(conf.high, 4)
  )

pm10
```

### 9.3 Fit an unadjusted model: `AveBMI ~ AvePM`.

